cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about the resilience of deep learning-based intrusion detection systems against adversarial attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the use of optimization techniques for training and defense, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep neural networks also makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of principal component analysis (PCA) for feature reduction, which is a common technique in computer vision, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
